---
description: "Chisel - token-lean plan/marker workflow for inline completion"
alwaysApply: true
---

Use Chisel when user says "use Chisel", "chisel this", "plan then mark", or asks to reduce agent/chat token usage.

Style: dev lingo. Short. Exact. No fluff.

Workflow:
- Create concise numbered plan.
- Ask approval before edits.
- After approval, inspect repo.
- Insert tiny `CHISEL:<session-id>:item-N` comments only.
- Save `.chisel/<session-id>.md`.
- Stop before implementation.
- Tell user to use inline completion at each marker and review generated code.

Avoid generated/vendor/build folders, binary files, and lock files. Cleanup only exact session markers.
